height=328 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/651490/extras/1389582c2cbbd99ee9711942bd0d108c.webm?t=1767798347\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/651490/extras/1389582c2cbbd99ee9711942bd0d108c.mp4?t=1767798347\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" style=\"text-align: center\"><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/651490/extras/909e6628f9746e66c1850bd6c21f8d4c.webp?t=1767798347\" width=600 height=42 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >No Longer Home was born when the developers were similarly forced apart after university, and decided to stay in touch by working on a game together. Development duo Hana and Cel chose this project as a way to explore and express the emotions that came with saying goodbye.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" style=\"text-align: center\"><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/651490/extras/cd40dc9c31f42f6ffa3e70547a291f92.poster.avif?t=1767798347\" width=600 height=338 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/651490/extras/cd40dc9c31f42f6ffa3e70547a291f92.webm?t=1767798347\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/651490/extras/cd40dc9c31f42f6ffa3e70547a291f92.mp4?t=1767798347\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" style=\"text-align: center\"><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/651490/extras/7b4f2168d78681e60e717122afc50e4c.webp?t=1767798347\" width=600 height=42 /></span><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay mut